        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Columbia </placeName><date when="1835-09-22">Septr 22nd 1835</date></p>
<p><persName>Jas. F. Perry Esqr</persName>-</p>
<p>Dear Sir,</p>
<p>at the request of <persName>Mr. J. H. Bell</persName>, I enclose you a copy of a letter writen
by <persName>Col. S. F. Austin</persName> to <persName>P. W. Grayson</persName> of this place; and should have sent
you a copy of the Cols, <hi rend="italic">circular</hi>, if time would have permited.&#8212; I have
sent a copy to the <persName>Committee of safety, at <placeName>Velasco</placeName></persName>, of which you are a
<persName>member</persName>, and one to <placeName>Brazoria</placeName>, for publication.&#8212; I shall leave tomorrow
for <placeName>Matagorda</placeName>, on business, but shall return before <date when="1835-10-05">Monday the 5th of next
month,</date> at which time I wish to have a meeting of the <persName>Ayuntamiento</persName>; you
will please attend.&#8212;</p>
<p><persName>A. Brigham</persName></p>


        </div1>
